2026-04-13 15:24:48,554 INFO RLM iteration 2/50
Reasoning: We inspected the workbook and found a single sheet 'Pay Items' with columns: A = Pay Item Number, B = UOM, C = Description. The user wants to be able to type a description in rows below a specific black row (likely rows 20‑26) and have the Pay Item Number and UOM automatically filled in the cells to the left. We'll implement this by adding formulas in columns A and B for rows 20‑26 that look up the entered description in the existing table (rows 3‑). We'll also color cells A20‑B26 with the requested hex color #FFF2CC. The formulas will return an empty string when the description cell is empty. After modifying the workbook we save it to the output directory.
Code:
```repl
import openpyxl
from openpyxl.styles import PatternFill
from pathlib import Path

# Paths
input_path = Path('/sandbox/input/input_spreadsheet/1_39667_init.xlsx')
output_dir = Path('/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet/')
output_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
output_path = output_dir / input_path.name

# Load workbook (keep formulas)
wb = openpyxl.load_workbook(input_path, data_only=False)
ws = wb.active  # Assuming the only sheet is the target

# Define the fill color for rows 20‑26, columns A & B
fill = PatternFill(start_color='FFF2CC', end_color='FFF2CC', fill_type='solid')

# Define the lookup range (use a generous upper bound to cover future rows)
lookup_start_row = 3
lookup_end_row = 1000  # enough rows for the lookup tables

# Helper to build the formula strings for a given row

def pay_item_formula(row):
    desc_cell = f"C{row}"
    # If description empty, return empty string
    return f"=IF({desc_cell}="", "", IFERROR(INDEX($A${lookup_start_row}:$A${lookup_end_row}, MATCH({desc_cell}, $C${lookup_start_row}:$C${lookup_end_row}, 0)), ""))"

def uom_formula(row):
    desc_cell = f"C{row}"
    return f"=IF({desc_cell}="", "", IFERROR(INDEX($B${lookup_start_row}:$B${lookup_end_row}, MATCH({desc_cell}, $C${lookup_start_row}:$C${lookup_end_row}, 0)), ""))"

# Apply to rows 20‑26
for r in range(20, 27):  # inclusive of 26
    # Set fill for A and B cells
    ws[f"A{r}"].fill = fill
    ws[f"B{r}"].fill = fill
    # Set formulas
    ws[f"A{r}"].value = pay_item_formula(r)
    ws[f"B{r}"].value = uom_formula(r)

# Save the modified workbook
wb.save(output_path)

print(f"Workbook saved to {output_path}")
```
